40|$|Abstract. This paper {{deals with}} {{complete}} hypersurfaces {{immersed in the}} (n + 1) -dimensional hyperbolic and steady state spaces. By applying a technique of S. T. Yau and imposing suitable conditions on both the r-th <b>mean</b> <b>curvatures</b> and on the norm of the gradient of the height function, we obtain Bernstein-type results {{in each of these}} ambient spaces. 1...|$|R
